TY  - JOUR
AU  - Heuer, Justus
AU  - Merkle, Christoph
AU  - Weber, Martin
T1  - Fooled by Randomness: Investor Perception of Fund Manager Skill*
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfw011
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 21
IS  - 2
SP  - 605
EP  - 635
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Return-chasing investors almost exclusively consider top-performing funds for their investment decisions. When drawing conclusions about the managerial skill of these top performers, they tend to neglect fund volatility and the cross-sectional information contained in the number of funds and the distribution of skill. In multiple surveys of sophisticated retail investors, we show that they do not fully understand the role of chance in experimental samples of fund populations. Respondents evaluate each fund in isolation and do not sufficiently account for fund volatility. They confuse risk taking with manager skill and are thus likely to over-allocate capital to lucky past winners.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfw011
ER  - 



