TY  - JOUR
AU  - Yang, Hanxue
AU  - Kanniainen, Juho
T1  - Jump and Volatility Dynamics for the S&amp;P 500: Evidence for Infinite-Activity Jumps with Non-Affine Volatility Dynamics from Stock and Option Markets*
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfw001
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 21
IS  - 2
SP  - 811
EP  - 844
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Relatively little is known about the empirical performance of infinite-activity Lévy jump models, especially with non-affine volatility dynamics. We use extensive empirical data sets to study how infinite-activity Variance Gamma and Normal Inverse Gaussian (NIG) jumps with affine and non-affine volatility dynamics improve goodness of fit and option pricing performance. With Markov Chain Monte Carlo, different model specifications are estimated using the joint information of the S&amp;P 500 index and the VIX. Our article provides clear evidence that a parsimonious non-affine model with NIG return jumps and a linear variance specification is particularly competitive, even during the recent crisis.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfw001
ER  - 



